  <h2 class="pokemon-title">
    <a href="/VersionCompatibility"><span>Pokémon Version Compatibility</span></a><span>▸</span><span>Generation III (WIP)</span>
  </h2>

  <p>This page lists all Pokémon Generation IV game versions and accessories for all consoles. It also explains what game versions are compatible.</p>

  <h4>DS Console</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>DS and DS Lite consoles are same world-wide and can play any game versions. Those consoles can play DS and GBA games, and transfer Pokémon from GBA to DS.</li>
    <li>DSi consoles exist in multiple versions based on region. They can play DS games from any language and any region. They can't play GBA games. They can only play DSi games from the region of the DSi console. There are no DSi Pokémon games.</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>DS Game Versions</h4>
  <div>Pokémon Diamond, Pearl, Platinum, HeartGold, SoulSilver games each have 7 versions based on language.</div>
  <ul>
    <li>
      English (The US, Canada, UK, Australia retail boxes are different, but the GBA cartridge content is the same.)
    </li>
    <li>Japanese</li>
    <li>French</li>
    <li>Italian</li>
    <li>Spanish</li>
    <li>German</li>
    <li>Korean</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Main Core Series</h5>
  <div>Pokémon Diamond, Pearl, Platinum, HeartGold, SoulSilver games each have 8 versions based on language and region.</div>
  <ul>
    <li><span class="bold">Japan:</span> Japanese language</li>
    <li><span class="bold">The Americas and Asia:</span> English language</li>
    <li><span class="bold">Europe and Oceania:</span> English, French, German, Italian or Spanish (Unchangeable)</li>
    <li><span class="bold">Korea:</span> Korean language</li>
  </ul>
  <div>
    A notable difference between Americas English version and Europe English version is that the Americas version has access to the Game Corner, while the Europe one doesn't.
  </div>

  <br>
  <h5>Pokémon Ranger Series</h5>
  <div>Pokémon Ranger, Pokémon Ranger: Shadows of Almia, Pokémon Ranger: Guardian Signs games each have 3 versions based on region.</div>
  <ul>
    <li><span class="bold">Japan:</span> Japanese language</li>
    <li><span class="bold">The Americas and Asia:</span> English language</li>
    <li><span class="bold">Europe and Oceania:</span> English, French, German, Italian or Spanish language (Changeable)</li>
  </ul>


  <br>
