  <h4>Wii Console</h4>
  <div>The Wii has 5 officially released versions.</div>
  <ul>
    <li><span class="bold">NTSC-J (Japan):</span> Japanese language (unchangeable)</li>
    <li><span class="bold">NTSC-J (Hong-Kong, Taiwan):</span> Traditional Chinese language (unchangeable)
      <ul><li>No Pokémon games were released for the Chinese WII.</li></ul></li>
    <li><span class="bold">NTSC-U (The Americas, Middle East, Southeast Asia):</span> TODO</li>
    <li><span class="bold">PAL (Europe, Oceania, Indian, African): TODO</span>
    <li><span class="bold">NTSC-K (South Korea):</span> Korean language (unchangeable)
      <ul><li>No Pokémon games were released for the Korean WII.</li></ul></li>
  </ul>
  <h2 style="color: #f0ad4e;text-shadow: 0.1em  0.1em 0 #000 !important;">Beyond this point, information is incorrect.</h2>



  <h4>Accessories</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><span class="bold">Wii Controllers:</span> They are the same world-wide and can be used on any console version.</li>
    <li><span class="bold">Memory Card:</span> They are the same world-wide and can be used on any console version. The same Memory Card can only contain information of a single region at once. Ex: It can't contain both a NTSC-J and NTSC-U saves at once.</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Game Versions</h4>
  <div>A Wii game is specific to a region and can only be played on a Wii of that region.</div>
  <br>
  <div>My Pokémon Ranch (without update) exists in 3 versions. Is is discontinued since Wii Shop Channel's shutdown on January 31, 2019. It can interact with Pokémon Diamond and Pearl of the same language. TODO: What happens after changing the language on PAL Wii?</div>
  <div>
    It can be used to obtain Phione and Mew.
  </div>
  <ul>
    <li><span class="bold">NTSC-J (Japan):</span> Japanese language</li>
    <li><span class="bold">NTSC-U (The Americas and Asia):</span> English language</li>
    <li><span class="bold">PAL (Europe and Oceania):</span> Uses the Wii language (English, German, French, Spanish, Italian).</li>
  </ul>

  <div>My Pokémon Ranch (updated) exists in 1 version: Japanese. Is is discontinued since Wii Shop Channel's shutdown on January 31, 2019. It can interact with Japanese Diamond, Pearl and Platinum.</div>
  <ul>
    <li><span class="bold">NTSC-J (Japan):</span> Japanese language</li>
  </ul>


  <div>Pokémon Battle Revolution exists in 4 versions. They can interact with DS games of the same language. It is notable for providing Soul Dew and rare berries such as Starf Berry. However, it offers no exclusive content.</div>
  <ul>
    <li><span class="bold">NTSC-J (Japan):</span> Japanese language.</li>
    <li><span class="bold">NTSC-U (The Americas and Asia):</span> English language.</li>
    <li><span class="bold">PAL (Europe and Oceania):</span> Uses the Wii language (English, German, French, Spanish, Italian).</li>
    <li><span class="bold">NTSC-J (Taiwan):</span> Chinese language. TODO: It is unknown if it can interact with DS games.</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Wii-Game Cube Interactions</h4>
  <div>
    All Wii (except Chinese and Korean) can play Game Cube games of the same region. However, Game Cube Pokémon games played on the Wii can't interact with other games because the Wii is not compatible with the Game Cube to GBA Link Cable.
  </div>

